      <h2 id="ka-rubric">DAMA KA rubric — Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        Per <a href="/resource?path=docs/adr/0001-adopt-dcam-dmbok-elements.md">ADR 0001</a> Wave 1, KA-tagged pages carry a consistent rubric — <strong>Purpose · Activities · Deliverables · Roles · Metrics · Maturity</strong>. The summaries below map each rubric section onto the detail above; like the rest of this page they are a first-cut provisional draft for <em>Compliance &amp; Risk WG</em> ratification.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          Formalise the PDTF trust framework's implicit security controls into a published, auditable workstream —
          KYC/KYB, DID key management, signature verification, revocation, and audit logging — operationalising
          <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/eur/2016/679/article/32">UK GDPR Art 32</a> for the shape of the
          PDTF ecosystem (see <a href="#overview">§1 Overview</a>).
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Activities</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Maintain each control's policy, checklist, and audit profile (<a href="#controls">§2</a>, <a href="#policy-checklist-audit">§4</a>).</li>
          <li>Run the per-firm security self-assessment checklist (<a href="#checklist">§4.2</a>).</li>
          <li>Conduct audits against the per-control audit profiles (<a href="#audit">§4.3</a>).</li>
          <li>Execute the five-phase incident response and trigger reviews on W3C-standard changes (<a href="#incident">§5</a>).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Deliverables</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>This framework, with a policy + checklist + audit profile per control (<a href="#policy-checklist-audit">§4</a>).</li>
          <li>The Assurance Level × control matrix (<a href="#al-mapping">§3</a>) and the incident-response procedure (<a href="#incident">§5</a>).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Roles</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Compliance &amp; Risk WG</strong> — owns the framework end to end (<a href="#governance">§6</a>).</li>
          <li><strong>Technical WG</strong> — cryptographic primitives and reference tooling.</li>
          <li><strong>Trust Registry Operator / Governance Authority</strong> — registry &amp; status-list infrastructure; status changes.</li>
          <li><strong>Accredited Issuers &amp; Verifiers</strong> — implement the controls at the AL they claim.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Metrics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Control coverage per Assurance Level claimed.</li>
          <li>Audit findings raised and closed per quarter.</li>
